06427nam a22008295i 9783110662900DE-B159720211027022714.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211027t20212021gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2021940045  a97831106629007 a10.1515/97831106629002doi  a(DE-B1597)521985  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh00aDifferences, Similarities and Meanings :bSemiotic Investigations of Contemporary Communication Phenomena /ced. by Nicolae-Sorin Drăgan. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (VI, 308 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aSemiotics, Communication and Cognition [SCC] ,x1867-0873 ;v3000tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tPart I: Theoretical advances -- tCommunication, listening, non-functionality -- tDifference and similarity in the I-Other relation: between two individuals or two singularities? A semioethic approach -- tGlobal semiotics and its developments in the direction of semioethics -- tThe relevance of the encyclopaedia. From semiosis to sedimentation and back again -- tCultural narrative identities and the entanglement of value systems -- tPart II: Applied Semiotics -- tA The digital age in semiotics and communication -- tLying as a transaction of value: explorations in semiosis and communication from a new perspective -- tEffective affective campaigns? An analysis of campaigns centered on Roma -- tB Political semiotics and communication -- tThe semiotics of extremism -- tThe dynamic aspect of the semiotic behavior of political actors in TV debates -- tC Communication, semiotics and multimodality -- tThe different rifles of audiovisual communication: a semiotics of foreshadowing and the case of Roberto Benigni -- tDifferences, similarities and changes of national identity signs in print advertisements. The advertising discourse as a mirror of locality and vice-versa -- tWhat’s in a nickname? Form and function of sports’ team nicknames -- tArchitecture and painting codes in the Annunciation. Oltenia (XVIIIth–XIXth centuries) -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn a world of global communication, where each one’s life depends increasingly on signs, language and communication, understanding how we relate and opening ourselves to otherness, to differences in all their forms and aspects is becoming more and more relevant. Today, we often understand the differences in terms of adversity or opposition and forget the value of the similarities.Semiotic approaches can provide a critical point of view and a more general reflection that can redefine some aspects of the discussion about the nature of these semiotic categories, differences and similarities. The dichotomy differences – similarities is fundamental to understanding the meaning-making mechanisms in language (De Saussure, 1966; Deleuze, 1995), as well as in other sign systems (Ponzio, 1995; Sebeok & Danesi, 2000). Meaning always appears in the “play of differences” (Derrida, 1978) and similarities. Therefore, the phenomena of similarities and differences must be considered complementary (Marcus, 2011).This book addresses and offers new perspectives for analyzing and understanding sensitive topics in the world of global communication (humanities education, responsive understanding of otherness, digital culture and new media power).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCommunication.  aCulture Studies.  aMedia Studies.  aSemiotics.1 aBankov, Kristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBird, Ioana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaba-Buzoianu, Corina, e